Peter Dada, Akure The National Campaign Council of the All Progressives Congress for Ondo State Governorship Election, on Sunday said the triumph of the partlin Ondo State was a well-deserved The organisation also debunked the media reports that the APC was involved in vote buying in the just concluded election. Speaking with journalists in Akure, on Sunday, the Secretary of the APC National Campaign Council, Ondo 2020, M. Mustapha Saliu, while dismissing the report said, “The problem is that we have bad losers. “We just finished election in Edo State and the party congratulated the governor. That is the spirit of sportsmanship and that is responsibility to the populace. But they are looking for flimsy excuses to just explain their poor performance. “I think it’s irresponsible and very petty on the part of the PDP. To a great extent, people came out to vote willingly, not because of inducement or any other thing. I want to believe that this is one of the best elections I have witnessed in this country.” Copyright PUNCH.
